<p>Question is a bit open, but I didn't find clear and simple answer.</p>  <p>When you add a lib with gradle in your Android studio, it is often that it brings many things you may not need for your project.</p>  <ul> <li>sub components you do not need</li> <li>dependencies already present in your project</li> <li>dependencies conflicting with other version in your project</li> <li>dependencies not used for our lib usage</li> </ul>  <p>1/ Does Gradle do everything for you (just keep what you need) ?</p>  <p>2/ How to exclude what you do not need ?</p>  <p>2-1/ How find library dependency and deal with it ?  (probably <a href="http://mvnrepository.com/" rel="nofollow">http://mvnrepository.com/</a>)</p>  <p>Please give us you best i class cook recipe.</p>